1. Move View to Shared Folder
Move _VehPopUp.cshtml from /Views/Vehicles/ to /Views/Shared/

2. Update Controller Action
csharp
// VehiclesController.cs
public ActionResult GetVehicleById(int id, bool readOnly = false)
{
    // ... existing logic ...
    return PartialView("~/Views/Shared/_VehPopUp.cshtml", vehicle);
}
3. Update JavaScript URLs
Modify all JavaScript references to use the correct action name:

javascript
// In loadVehicleForm function
$.get('@Url.Action("GetVehicleById", "Vehicles")', { id: vehicleId }, ...)

// In openEstimatePopup function
loadTabContent(
    "vehicleTabContent", 
    '@Url.Action("GetVehicleById", "Vehicles")', 
    { id: vehicleId },
    function() { ... }
);

// In onTabSelect configuration
var tabsConfig = [
    { 
        id: "vehicleTabContent", 
        url: '@Url.Action("GetVehicleById", "Vehicles")' 
    },
    // ... other tabs ...
];
4. Verify Tab Strip Initialization
Ensure your tab strip initialization properly handles the first tab:

javascript
// In document.ready
$("#estimateTabs").kendoTabStrip({
    animation: { open: { effects: "fadeIn" } },
    select: onTabSelect,
    activate: function(e) {
        // Load first tab immediately
        if ($(e.item).index() === 0 && $("#vehicleTabContent").is(":empty")) {
            loadTabContent(
                "vehicleTabContent", 
                '@Url.Action("GetVehicleById", "Vehicles")',
                { id: currentVehicleId }
            );
        }
    }
});
5. Update Partial View Paths
In _VehPopUp.cshtml, update any partial references that might be vehicle-specific:

html
<!-- Change -->
@Html.Partial("_SomePartial")

<!-- To -->
@Html.Partial("~/Views/Shared/_SomePartial.cshtml")
Why This Works:
Consistent Naming: JavaScript now references GetVehicleById instead of VehPopUp

Absolute View Path: Controller explicitly specifies shared view location

Proper URL Generation: Url.Action ensures correct route generation

First-tab Loading: Tab strip's activate event handles initial load

